        <updateDate>2021-09-29T18:15:27Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Flight Sharing Freedom Act </strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation to issue or revise regulations to ensure that a pilot who holds a pilot certificate may communicate with the public, in any manner, to facilitate an aircraft flight for which the pilot and passengers share aircraft operating expenses.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill excludes from common carrier regulations pilots who wish to coordinate flights and share aircraft operating expenses with passengers.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
